  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mHigh[0m

[30;1m702 | [0m[35m    .. __: https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/encryption-options.html[0m
[30;1m703 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m704 | [0m[35m    Using `!None` as *algorithm* will result in querying the server to know the[0m
[30;1m705 | [0m[35m    current server password encryption setting, which is a blocking operation:[0m

[30;1m707 | [0m[35m    want to maintain a non-blocking behaviour.[0m

[30;1m886 | [0m[35m`~cursor.itersize` now controls how many records are fetched at time[0m
[30;1m887 | [0m[35mduring the iteration: the default value of 2000 allows to fetch about 100KB[0m
[30;1m888 | [0m[35mper roundtrip assuming records of 10-20 columns of mixed number and strings;[0m

[30;1m88 | [0m[35mWhy does `!cursor.execute()` raise the exception *can't adapt*?[0m
[30;1m89 | [0m[35m    Psycopg converts Python objects in a SQL string representation by looking[0m
[30;1m90 | [0m[35m    at the object class.  The exception is raised when you are trying to pass[0m
[30;1m91 | [0m[35m    as query parameter an object for which there is no adapter registered for[0m
[30;1m92 | [0m[35m    its class.  See :ref:`adapting-new-types` for informations.[0m
[30;1m93 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m40 | [0m[35m.. cssclass:: faq[0m
[30;1m41 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m42 | [0m[35mWhy does `!psycopg2` leave database sessions "idle in transaction"?[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35m    Psycopg normally starts a new transaction the first time a query is[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35m    executed, e.g. calling `cursor.execute()`, even if the command is a[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35m    :sql:`SELECT`.  The transaction is not closed until an explicit[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m    `~connection.commit()` or `~connection.rollback()`.[0m

[30;1m385 | [0m[35m        exception.  Any unhandled exception will make it break out of the loop[0m
